5. The Missing Ending: The Final Unapproved Method
The current system has perfected the art of filtering out the one thing it once pretended to enable: widespread, meaningful participation.
It rewards:
	‚Ä¢	scale over access
	‚Ä¢	waste over efficiency
	‚Ä¢	capital over curiosity
	‚Ä¢	permanence over resolution
The only viable strategy is paradoxical:
To participate meaningfully, mine small.‚Ä®To compete seriously, burn big.‚Ä®To maintain sanity, choose the first and accept irrelevance.
In other words:
